Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Saute onion until tender. Stir in potatoes, soup, milk, cheese, bell pepper, black pepper, and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs. Transfer to a 2 quart casserole dish and top with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.